  "text": "The common type of bacteria is Escherichia coli (E. coli) [CITATION_1] . Its behavior and movement come from a set of six rigid spinning (100-200 r.p.s) flagella, each driven as a biological motor. An E. coli bacterium alternates through running and tumbling, the chemotactic actions of the bacteria are modeled as follows:",
